  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Females have a lower incidence of hypertensive and cardiovascular disorders that may relate
      to differences in nitrogen oxides in the blood and saliva. Some nitrogen oxides are recycled
      with the help of oral bacteria to nitric oxide which is protective against vascular
      disorders. This study will test the hypothesis that females have different numbers and
      species of these nitrogen-oxide reducing bacteria.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
